Forms are used to take the input from an user and process the input using some scripting language.
<form>
Username : <input type="text" name="uname" size="3" maxlegth="5'/>
Password : <input type="password" name="upass" />
Gender : <input type="radio" name="gender" value="male" checked/>Male
         <input type="radio" name="gender" value="female"/>Female
Course : <input type"checkbox" name="course" value="HTML" checked/>HTML
         <input type"checkbox" name="course" value="CSS" checked/>CSS
Age Group : <select name="age">
<option>10-20</option>
<option>20-30</option>
<option>30-40</option>
<option>40-50</option>
</select>
Comments : <textarea name="comments" rows="5" cols="10"></textarea>
</form>

NOTE: As default for radio and checkbox none came as selected, to opt for any option to come as selected we uses checked property.
